<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14080">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Crime%20Prevention.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-12904">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      <b>Laws and Society.</b> Discuss the following with your counselor:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12904 mb-requirement-id-12907">
        (a) Why we have criminal laws. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/j9IvbB50YB0" target="_blank"
          >The Purposes of Criminal Law (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12904 mb-requirement-id-12908">
        (b) What are types of crimes, including property crimes, crimes against
        people, white collar crime, and environmental crime. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/BSyY9RRR6ds" target="_blank"
          >7 Types of Crime (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12904 mb-requirement-id-12909">
        (c) Why people commit crimes. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/1FD7aMivAek" target="_blank"
          >Why Do People Commit Crimes? (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12904 mb-requirement-id-12910">
        (d) Why everyone should follow the law even when no one is watching.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/PgaLe64jUJk?si=X49W-2QPhOORpk9o"
          target="_blank"
          >Why Do We Obey Laws? The Social Contract (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/Ax2Ig6Y9Ve4?si=BL7BGjL2Flj6DSyV"
          target="_blank"
          >Our Social Contract to Follow the Law (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12904 mb-requirement-id-12911">
        (e) What is the meaning of crime prevention. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/RbObl2KKU7A?si=03soZBeN05po0MOv"
          target="_blank"
          >What is Crime Prevention? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/PS1RmeyTSD0?si=OoWp68p1BqHgG9Hj"
          target="_blank"
          >Basic Crime Prevention (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-12905">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      <b>Groups Working to Prevent Crime.</b> Research how the following groups
      contribute to crime prevention and share your findings with your
      counselor:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12905 mb-requirement-id-12912">
        (a) Citizens, including youth <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/WxWrbx0dmzc" target="_blank"
          >Neighbors: The Key to Crime Prevention (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/eVZ-NOoyIIE?si=h1_TsiWRVwr42Kg9"
          target="_blank"
          >How Sport Helps to Prevent Crime (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12905 mb-requirement-id-12913">
        (b) Schools <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/qvjG3lmM3Gk" target="_blank"
          >Education Efforts Could Prevent Crime (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/RkMHmdFPkI0?si=kNVJpoq5KCe6R8EC"
          target="_blank"
          >Preventing Crime with Education (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12905 mb-requirement-id-12914">
        (c) Neighborhood, social and civic groups, including youth groups
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/lx2wS94nk_Q" target="_blank"
          >Youth Programs Teach Conflict Resolution Skills (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/rhk1Yo_mCvA?si=BtB_95Orw4SFKUOq"
          target="_blank"
          >Youth Programs Reduce Crime (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12905 mb-requirement-id-12915">
        (d) Private security <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/EGPbHVf-rXc?si=dPcuFJxAjOw8SxE2"
          target="_blank"
          >Security Guards Reduce Crime in LA (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/sWHSndoE1U0?si=oOYuRrMomUJShgYY"
          target="_blank"
          >Private Security and Crime Prevention (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12905 mb-requirement-id-12916">
        (e) Law enforcement agencies <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/UCMgXMc-So8" target="_blank"
          >What is Community Policing? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/TqWdlDABmvo" target="_blank"
          >Community Policing (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12905 mb-requirement-id-12917">
        (f) Courts <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/whgh6FD53wI" target="_blank"
          >Problem-Solving Courts (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/TYTiGwoQLKI?si=JA8KETAC8HTA8JXV"
          target="_blank"
        >
          Colorado's 1st JD Problem Solving Courts (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12905 mb-requirement-id-12918">
        (g) Corrections and rehabilitation programs <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Fb-gOS3p44U" target="_blank"
          >How Norway Reinvented Prison (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/Awgq2rQFm34?si=1_3-dFa9TWAL4stU"
          target="_blank"
          >Humane Incarceration (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-12877">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      <b>Crime in Your Community, State, and Nation.</b> Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12877 mb-requirement-id-12878">
        (a) With your parent or guardian's permission and the approval of your
        counselor, research local, state, or national news coverage of three
        crimes of different types. Research how common these types of crimes are
        in your state or in the United States. <br /><i>Resources:</i
        ><a
          href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XmqL65ZBx44&amp;t=23s"
          target="_blank"
          >5 Incredible Prison Rehabilitation Programs (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2024/04/24/what-the-data-says-about-crime-in-the-us/"
          target="_blank"
          >What the Data Says About Crime in the U.S. and Substances (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/shorts/_W__yWCaCW0" target="_blank"
          >Top 5 Common Crimes in the USA (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12877 mb-requirement-id-12879">
        (b) Record notes on which law enforcement agencies and courts were
        involved in the pursuit of justice for the victims and the accused
        person, why you think these crimes were committed, and what could be
        done to prevent similar crimes. Review your research with your
        counselor.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-12881">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      <b>Home and Neighborhood Crime Prevention.</b> Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12881 mb-requirement-id-12882">
        (a) Discuss the following with your counselor:
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12882 mb-requirement-id-12919">
        (1) How participation in activities of families, churches, sports teams,
        and clubs prevents crime. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/GG5UkPNxBHU?si=4vsdLjvlfQEauAOD"
          target="_blank"
          >Church members Escape Crime-Ridden Lives (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/oEJoZnsgUZA?si=eaTS6FuXVW2mndEo"
          target="_blank"
          >How Can Boxing Clubs Help Prevent Crime (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12882 mb-requirement-id-12920">
        (2) How designs of houses, neighborhoods, public buildings, stores,
        streets, and parks prevent crime. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/p3UY1w1O3PA" target="_blank"
          >What is CPTED? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/CZ5sVtt9-8I" target="_blank"
          >Designing Out Crime: CPTED (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12881 mb-requirement-id-12883">
        (b) Conduct a security survey of a home, a neighborhood, a park, or a
        camp building with adult supervision and following youth protection
        guidelines using a security checklist in the
        <em>Crime Prevention</em> merit badge pamphlet or one approved by your
        counselor.<br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Requirement%20Resources/Crime%20Prevention/Home%20Security%20Checklists%20%231%20%232.pdf"
          target="_blank"
          >Home Security Checklists # 1 and # 2 (PDF)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Requirement%20Resources/Crime%20Prevention/Camp%20Security%20Checklists%20%231%20%232%2001%202026.pdf"
          target="_blank"
          >Camp Security Checklists # 1 and # 2 (PDF)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12881 mb-requirement-id-12921">
        (c) Use information from your survey for requirement 4(b) and the EDGE
        method to develop a lesson about how a family or Scouts can protect
        themselves from crime. Review your teaching plan with your counselor,
        then present your lesson to your family or to Scouts. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://www.scouting.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Teaching-Edge-Method.pdf"
          target="_blank"
          >The EDGE Method of Teaching (PDF)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-12906">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      <b>Retail Crime Prevention.</b> Research the following topics and review
      them with your counselor:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12906 mb-requirement-id-12922">
        (a) The impact of shoplifting and employee theft (also known as
        shrinkage) and loss prevention on retail finances, customer service, and
        reputation. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/sQ3m5T4vk3E" target="_blank"
          >The Impact of Shoplifting on the Retail Industry (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12906 mb-requirement-id-12923">
        (b) Techniques used by retail stores to prevent shoplifting. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/j4OJtL7Snko" target="_blank"
          >How to Prevent Shoplifting (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/giFprF8nsKg" target="_blank"
          >Retail Loss Prevention Techniques (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-12884">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      <b>Reporting Crime.</b> Discuss the following with your counselor:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12884 mb-requirement-id-12885">
        (a) When and how to report a crime or an impending crime. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/uPWW3S_LLT4" target="_blank"
          >How to Report a Crime (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/aMT6wlCOvEM" target="_blank"
          >How to Report a Crime - Public Safety Minute (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12884 mb-requirement-id-12886">
        (b) The warning signs for child abuse and domestic violence and how to
        report these situations.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12884 mb-requirement-id-12924">
        (c) The three R's of personal safety and protection and how to apply
        them.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12884 mb-requirement-id-12925">
        (d) How reporting a crime can help law enforcement provide resources for
        crime victims. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/vZbarQJTs1c" target="_blank"
          >Importance of Reporting Crime (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-12888">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 7. </span>
      <b>Peers and Crime.</b> Discuss the following with your counselor:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12888 mb-requirement-id-12889">
        (a) The role that peers play in crime, crime prevention, and
        experiencing crime. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/2Q4tlPEihAM?si=Ov5f_cNp8hXWWKj3"
          target="_blank"
          >Adolescent Risk-Takers: The Power of Peers (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12888 mb-requirement-id-12890">
        (b) How to resist peer influence. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/R3LV5oZPof4?si=OaDJ9tyF9HHGEgu6"
          target="_blank"
          >Positive Peer Influences (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/SNZ9LHclUvA" target="_blank"
          >Managing Peer Pressure (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12888 mb-requirement-id-12926">
        (c) Bullying and hazing behaviors and signs that a friend may be
        bullying you or someone else. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/4mrE5zgEvt4?si=_KsJzcDzgFI1sPZ3"
          target="_blank"
          >Protect Yourself Rules - Bullying (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/eAj2kTQyEGw?si=L8hRIgQlj7BzD3Qc"
          target="_blank"
          >The Basics of Bullying (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/ffzIhWoi5ac" target="_blank"
          >Bullying and How to Stop it (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12888 mb-requirement-id-12927">
        (d) Explain the impact of gangs on communities. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youth.gov/youth-topics/preventing-gang-involvement/adverse-effects"
          target="_blank"
          >How Gangs Affect Communities (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-12891">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 8. </span>
      <b>Substance Use and Crime.</b> Discuss the following with your counselor:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12891 mb-requirement-id-12892">
        (a) The legal and health consequences of using alcohol, tobacco and
        vaping products, illegal drugs, and diverted prescription drugs.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/hBC7i-vHWsU?si=fJxR4B27CYpbWGcz"
          target="_blank"
          >The Science of Addiction (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/9dZS_Rniak0?si=V6A0VHuwIyUIe8ew"
          target="_blank"
          >Electronic Cigarettes and Vaping (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Y4xITbvN7rk" target="_blank"
          >Legal Consequences of Drugs (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/b6Dte96WdqM?si=t3-nEWs-vlLETkqL"
          target="_blank"
          >Drug Abuse, Causes, Signs and Symptoms, Diagnosis and Treatment
          (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12891 mb-requirement-id-12893">
        (b) How substance use contributes to violence and property crime and
        increases a person's risk of becoming a victim of crime. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://ncaddnational.org/addiction_articles/alcohol-drugs-and-crime/"
          target="_blank"
          >Drugs and Crime (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://drugabusestatistics.org/drug-related-crime-statistics/"
          target="_blank"
          >Crimes Related to Drugs (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12891 mb-requirement-id-12894">
        (c) How drug abuse awareness, prevention, and recovery programs help
        prevent crime. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/ATaSk7NzXLc" target="_blank"
          >Reduce Crime AND Save Money (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12891 mb-requirement-id-12895">
        (d) How to get help if you or someone you know needs help with drugs or
        alcohol. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://findtreatment.gov/" target="_blank"
          >Finding Help for Drug and Alcohol Disorders (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/IcLtRTEP7eo" target="_blank"
          >Treatment Choices for Substance Use Disorders (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-12899">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 9. </span>
      <b>Online Crime and You.</b> Discuss the following with your counselor:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12899 mb-requirement-id-12900">
        (a) How to avoid being the victim of online crimes. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/_IELMnzqVgQ?si=zQ2ST7Jk5EBcUpPo"
          target="_blank"
          >Top 10 Cyber Crimes (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://consumer.ftc.gov/protect-your-personal-information-hackers-scammers#keep"
          target="_blank"
          >Protect Your Personal Information From Hackers and Scammers
          (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12899 mb-requirement-id-12901">
        (b) Common online financial scams. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/k8UVnkh8i0c" target="_blank"
          >Common Online Scams (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12899 mb-requirement-id-12902">
        (c) Effective online security. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/aO858HyFbKI?si=ynzNZIiw7gdY8d3r"
          target="_blank"
          >Effective Online Security (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/YPSAT/YT%20Mod1%20Final%20Master%20Small.mp4?_gl=1*1npxm9d*_ga*MTk1Mzg0NzM1OS4xNzU1NjM1NDc0*_ga_20G0JHESG4*czE3NTc2MjAyMjAkbzIxJGcxJHQxNzU3NjIwMjU2JGoyNCRsMCRoMA..*_gcl_au*MTU0OTgwNjcyLjE3NTU2MzU0NzQ.&amp;_ga=2.243209291.839854577.1757346029-1953847359.1755635474"
          target="_blank"
          >Digital Safety (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12899 mb-requirement-id-12903">
        (d) Identity theft and how to prevent it. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/kDFeSUUwRnA" target="_blank"
          >Preventing Identity Theft (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/zq8ErbZzcbI" target="_blank"
          >How to Prevent Identity Theft (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12899 mb-requirement-id-12928">
        (e) How criminals use social media to target victims. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/5bdBvNCBeho?si=qbnnwkHshfttTu8f"
          target="_blank"
          >How Criminals Use Social Media (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-12899 mb-requirement-id-12929">
        (f) How bullying, texting, and sharing photos can become crimes.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.scouting.org/training/youth/bullying/"
          target="_blank"
          >Bullying Awareness (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.stopbullying.gov/" target="_blank"
          >Prevention: Learn How to Identify Bullying and Stand Up to It Safely
          (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/0Xo8N9qlJtk?si=9EbwzuBmLSEyDL-c"
          target="_blank"
          >Top 10 Forms of Cyber Bullying (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/YPSAT/YT%20Mod2%20Final%20Master%20Small.mp4"
          target="_blank"
          >Bullying (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-12930">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 10. </span>
      <b>Interview.</b> With your parent or guardian's permission and your
      counselor's approval, interview a law enforcement officer or a civil
      servant about their work in crime prevention. Learn about how they chose
      this career and about their duties. Discuss what you learned with your
      counselor.
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-12931">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 11. </span>
      <b>Careers.</b> Identify three career opportunities that would use skills
      and knowledge in the field of crime prevention. Pick one and research the
      training, education, certification requirements, experience, and expenses
      associated with entering the field. Research the prospects for employment,
      starting salary, advancement opportunities and career goals associated
      with this career. Discuss what you learned with your counselor and whether
      you might be interested in this career. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/eqTjWF4GRm0?si=rRKOb3rTcAHM4CpT" target="_blank"
        >8 Careers in Criminal Justice (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/kR-yLbFoR9A?si=gdzqOCdcfn32XOD_" target="_blank"
        >How Law Enforcement Agencies Serve the Public (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
